summary: This is a domestic witness travel request form from an AUSA to the SDNY Victim/Witness Unit, dated November 12, 2021, for a witness in the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The witness is scheduled to travel to appear for trial from November 26 to December 1, 2021, and is identified as a victim-witness.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell, which is the subject of this witness travel request.

persons.name: Ed Tyrrell
persons.context: Mentioned in the instructions as a contact for questions about witness travel funding for investigative interviews.

events.title: Witness Scheduled Trial Appearance
events.description: A fact witness, identified as a victim-witness, is scheduled to arrive in SDNY to appear for the trial in United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Witness Scheduled Departure
events.description: The scheduled departure date for the fact witness traveling for the Maxwell trial.

keyFacts: A witness travel request was filed on November 12, 2021, for a victim-witness to testify at the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.
The witness was scheduled to be in SDNY from November 26 to December 1, 2021, specifically for trial testimony.
The witness is identified as a 'Fact Witness' and a 'Victim-Witness', but their identity is not disclosed in this form.
The document references standard DOJ procedures (Instruction 1300.01.01) for witness travel and funding.
